The **architecture direction** for the solution — high-level only. This sets the *shape* and the
one or two choices that are **expensive to reverse**. It deliberately stops short of detailed design.

> **Design-depth boundary.** R&D owns *direction and constraints*; the `planner`
> owns *detailed module/interface design, file layout, and PR-sized slices*. If this document starts
> specifying function signatures or per-file plans, it has overstepped — that work will be redone by
> the planner and will go stale here. Keep it to direction crisp enough to plan from.

